<paragraph id="8BCC36A6FF858C3ABFB5D19BFBA1F884" blockId="1.[151,1437,1583,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
a) The name [
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF858C3ABE15D19BFE29F958" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[359,441,1692,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF858C3ABE15D19BFE29F958" box="[359,441,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF858C3ABEBED19BFD4AF958" authority="Hubner, [1804]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1804" box="[460,730,1691,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ausonia">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF858C3ABEBED19BFDB5F95B" box="[460,549,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">ausonia</emphasis>
Hübner, [1804]
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF858C3ABC6AD19CFC5AF958" author="Hemming, A. F." box="[792,970,1691,1718]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refId="ref6166" refString="Hemming, A. F. (1937) Hubner. A bibliographical and systematic account of the entomological works of Jacob Hubner and of the supplements thereto by Carl Geyer, Gottfried Franz von Frolich and Gottlieb August Wilhelm Herrich-Schaffer. Vol. 1 &amp; 2. Royal entomological Society, London, xxxiv + 605 pp. &amp; 274 pp." type="book" year="1937">Hemming 1937</bibRefCitation>
) was published on Pl. 113 of Papiliones, as caption to Figs 582 and 583. In the (very partial) text of the ‘Sammlung’, which appeared only in [1805-6], we are informed (p. 65) that the depicted specimen came from ‘Italien’ and was preserved under the name “Ausonia” in Abbot Mazzola’s collection. Together with Schiffermüller’s collection and many other materials, Ab. Vincenz Mazzola’s collection, bequeathed to the Naturhistorisches Museum (Vienna), was destroyed in the 
<date id="FFCD1066FF858C3ABA73D02CFA0CF8A8" box="[1281,1436,1835,1862]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" value="1848-10">October 1848</date>
bombardment of the centre of Vienna and ensuing fire (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF858C3ABC42D057FBB4F884" author="Horn, W. &amp; Kahle, I. &amp; Friese, G. &amp; Gaedicke, R." box="[816,1060,1871,1898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refId="ref6504" refString="Horn, W., Kahle, I., Friese, G. &amp; Gaedicke, R. (1990) Collectiones entomologicae. Ein Kompendium uber den Verbleib entomologischer Sammlungen der Welt bis 1960. Vols. 1 - 2. Akademie der Landwirtschaftswissenschaften der DDR, Berlin, 53 pp. 128 figs., 38 pls. [pp. 1 - 220, 1 fig. &amp; pp. 221 - 573, 38 pls., 127 figs.]" type="book" year="1990">
Horn 
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF858C3ABC03D057FC32F884" box="[881,930,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">et al</emphasis>
. 1990: 256
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC36A6FF858C3ABFB5D073FC4AF814" blockId="1.[151,1437,1583,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
[Note. Hübner ([1806: 64-65]) in his text referred to Figs 416 and 582-583 as belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF858C3ABBA4D073FABFF863" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1804" box="[1238,1327,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ausonia">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF858C3ABBA4D073FABFF863" box="[1238,1327,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">ausonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Fig. 416 representing the male, Figs. 582-583 the female. However, only Figs 582-583 can be attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF858C3ABBA4D09FFABFF85F" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1804" box="[1238,1327,1944,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ausonia">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF858C3ABBA4D09FFABFF85F" box="[1238,1327,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">ausonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since for Fig. 416 Hübner had previously used (in [1800]) the name “belia” in the caption of Pl. Pap 83. The latter specimen must be regarded as a 
<typeStatus id="54C88804FF858C3ABEE3D0E7FE78F814" box="[401,488,2016,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF858C3ABD7FD0E7FCD1F814" authority="Kirby, 1871" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1871" box="[525,833,2015,2042]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="esperi">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF858C3ABD7FD0E7FD24F817" box="[525,692,2016,2042]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Euchloe esperi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF858C3ABDC9D0D8FCD1F814" author="Kirby, W. F." box="[699,833,2015,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" refId="ref7024" refString="Kirby, W. F. (1871) A synonymic catalogue of diurnal Lepidoptera. John van Voorst, London, viii + 883 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11905" type="book" year="1871">Kirby, 1871</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see below)].
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0C662EFF868C39BFE5D1B1FCFAF86C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842458" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3842458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842458/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" startId="2.[151,250,1718,1743]" targetBox="[160,1421,191,1687]" targetPageId="2">
