(NHMUK). (E). Lectotype (♂) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF868C39BC37D040FB4FF8B1" authority="Kirby, 1871" authorityName=", Kirby" authorityYear="1871" box="[837,1247,1862,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="ausonia" variety="esperi">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF868C39BC37D040FC7FF8B1" box="[837,1007,1863,1887]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Euchloe ausonia</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF868C39BB53D04FFBCFF8B1" box="[1057,1119,1864,1887]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">esperi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF868C39BB14D041FB4FF8B1" author="Kirby, W. F." box="[1126,1247,1862,1887]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" refId="ref7024" refString="Kirby, W. F. (1871) A synonymic catalogue of diurnal Lepidoptera. John van Voorst, London, viii + 883 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11905" type="book" year="1871">Kirby, 1871</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(5) (NMI). Labels relative to the illustrated specimens are shown on the right of each row.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCC36A6FF878C38BFB5D79EFB0DFE41" blockId="3.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
b) Since the taxonomic interpretation of Hübner’s pictures is far from being unequivocal, because differences between adults of the 1 
<superScript id="7C069BEEFF878C38BEE4D7BBFE31FF24" attach="left" box="[406,417,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">st</superScript>
and 2 
<superScript id="7C069BEEFF878C38BE96D7BBFE64FF24" attach="left" box="[484,500,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">nd</superScript>
generation of both the eastern and the western ‘dappled whites’ are strong, and since truly diagnostic species-specific differences are found only in the preimaginal stages (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BBF8D7E6FA94FF15" author="Back, W." box="[1162,1284,225,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="225 - 243" refId="ref4912" refString="Back, W. (1979) Zur Biologie der europaischen und nord west afrikanischen Populationen von Euchloe ausonia Hubner 1804 (Lep. Pieridae). Atalanta, 10 (3), 225 - 243, figs 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1979">Back 1979</bibRefCitation>
) and in DNA COI sequences (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BE08D602FDA4FEF1" author="Back, W. &amp; Miller, M. A. &amp; Opler, O. A." box="[378,564,261,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref5008" refString="Back, W., Miller, M. A. &amp; Opler, O. A. (2011) Genetic, phenetic, and distributional relationships of Nearctic Euchloe (Pieridae, Pierinae, Anthocharidini). Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 65 (1), 1 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.18473 / lepi. v 65 i 1. a 1" type="journal article" year="2011">
Back 
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF878C38BEC8D601FE62FEF1" box="[442,498,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), this name was taken to represent each of the already mentioned taxa, at various taxonomic ranks, depending on authors. More precisely, the name [
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF878C38BCDBD62EFC6BFEAD" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[937,1019,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF878C38BCDBD62EFC6BFEAD" box="[937,1019,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF878C38BB79D62DFA83FEAD" authority="Hubner, [1804]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1804" box="[1035,1299,296,323]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ausonia">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF878C38BB79D62DFBF4FEAD" box="[1035,1124,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">ausonia</emphasis>
Hübner, [1804]
</taxonomicName>
was applied either i) to the ‘western dappled white’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BD26D64AFCA9FE89" author="Ochsenheimer, F." box="[596,825,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" refId="ref7232" refString="Ochsenheimer, F. (1808) Die Schmetterlinge von Europa. 1 (2). G. Fleischer der Junger, Leipzig, xxx + 240 + [1] pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 50612" type="book" year="1808">Ochsenheimer 1808</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BC36D64AFC6DFE89" author="Staudinger, O." box="[836,1021,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref7496" refString="Staudinger, O. (1901) Erster Theil: Famil. Papilionidae-Hepialidae. In: Staudinger, O. &amp; Rebel, H., Catalog der Lepidopteren des Palaearktischen Faunengebietes. Dritte Auflage. R. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, pp. i-xxxii + 1 - 411. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 120482" type="book chapter" year="1901">Staudinger 1901</bibRefCitation>
, etc.), or ii) to the ‘mountain dappled white’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BF9CD676FEE4FE65" author="Kirby, W. F." box="[238,372,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" refId="ref7024" refString="Kirby, W. F. (1871) A synonymic catalogue of diurnal Lepidoptera. John van Voorst, London, viii + 883 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11905" type="book" year="1871">Kirby 1871</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BEF0D676FDD0FE65" author="Rothschild, W." box="[386,576,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="301 - 305" refId="ref7431" refString="Rothschild, W. (1914) A preliminary account of the Lepidopteran Fauna of Guelt-es-Stel, Central Algeria, Novitates Zoologicae, 21, 301 - 305. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 16331" type="journal article" year="1914">Rothschild 1914</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BD3FD676FD67FE65" author="Oberthur, C." box="[589,759,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="51 - 61" refId="ref7207" refString="Oberthur, C. (1914) Anthocharis crameri Butler. Etudes de Lepidopterologie comparee, 10, 51 - 61. [texted]" type="journal article" year="1914">Oberthür 1914</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BC76D676FC28FE65" author="Hemming, F. A." box="[772,952,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="493 - 504" refId="ref6087" refString="Hemming, F. A. (1931) New material regarding the dates of the plates of the Papiliones in Jacob Hubner's &quot; Sammlung europaischer Schmetterlinge &quot;, with notes on the synonymy and type localities of certain species described therein. Transactions of the entomological Society of London, 79 (3), 493 - 504. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1931. tb 00713. x" type="journal article" year="1931">Hemming 1931</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BCB4D676FBFCFE65" author="Bernardi, G." box="[966,1132,368,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="66 - 103" refId="ref5169" refString="Bernardi, G. (1945) Etudes sur le genre Euchloe Hb. (Lep. Pieridae). Miscellanea entomologica; Revue entomologique internationale, 42 (6), 66 - 103, pls. IV-VI." type="journal article" year="1945">Bernardi 1945</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BB08D676FB25FE65" author="Bernardi, G." box="[1146,1205,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref5209" refString="Bernardi, G. (1947) La nomenclature de quelques formes europeennes de l' Euchloe ausonia Hb. (= belia Auct.). Miscellanea entomologica; Revue entomologique internationale, 44 (1), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1947">1947</bibRefCitation>
, Forster &amp; Wohlfart 1955, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BFAFD692FEE8FE41" author="Higgins, L. G." box="[221,376,404,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" refId="ref6364" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1975) The classification of European butterflies. Collins, London, 320 pp., 60 pls." type="book" year="1975">Higgins 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BEF1D692FE2FFE41" author="Higgins, L. G." box="[387,447,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="246" refId="ref6390" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1980) Nomenclature of the dappled whites (Lepidoptera: Pieridae). Entomologist's Gazette, 31 (4), 246." type="journal article" year="1980">1980</bibRefCitation>
), or finally iii) to the ‘eastern dappled white’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BCB3D692FBDAFE41" author="Verity, R." box="[961,1098,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="169 - 171" refId="ref7757" refString="Verity, R. (1923) The nomenclature of the European Euchloe ausonia, Hb. (= belia, Auct. nec L.). Entomologist's Record and Journal of Variation, 35 (11), 169 - 171." type="journal article" year="1923">Verity 1923</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B57FF878C38BB27D692FB01FE41" author="Verity, R." box="[1109,1169,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="20 - 37" refId="ref7801" refString="Verity, R. (1947) Le Farfalle diurne d'Italia. Vol. 3. Divisione Papilionida, Sezione Papilionina, Famiglie Papilionidae e Pieridae. Marzocco, Firenze, xvi + 381 pp., pls. 20 - 37 + x-xiv." type="book chapter" year="1947">1947</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC36A6FF878C38BFB5D6BEFE35FDD1" blockId="3.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
Summarising, it is exclusively on the subjective interpretation of Hübner’s figures and on the derivation of its name from the land where the ancient people of the Ausoni used to live, i.e. in central and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3647636FF878C38BB8BD6DAFABDFE19" box="[1273,1325,477,503]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Italy</collectingCountry>
, that [
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF878C38BA06D6D9FF5AFDF5" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF878C38BA06D6D9FF5AFDF5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D25FF878C38BFA8D505FE73FDF5" authority="Hubner, [1804]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1804" box="[218,483,512,539]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ausonia">
<emphasis id="B907EAB4FF878C38BFA8D505FEA3FDF5" box="[218,307,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">ausonia</emphasis>
Hübner, [1804]
</taxonomicName>
is now considered the correct name to identify the butterfly colloquially known as the ‘eastern dappled white’.
</paragraph>
